CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 13, 1960, pg. 28 reads: "Two Champions - Batting champion Hank Aaron of the Milwaukee Braves was all ears at the Dapper Dan sports banquet Sunday night as he received a few pointers on football from Pete Dimperio, Westinghouse High School coach, who knows a thing or two about winning titles himself."
TitMainTitle: Westinghouse High School football coach Pete Dimperio and Milwaukee Braves baseball player Hank Aaron holding football, at Pittsburgh Dapper Dan banquet in Hilton Hotel
